reviews.review_text: This location of Canadian Tire is one of the best location and free parking. They are located independently along with other brand names like Sports Check, Best Buy, Marshals. There is a Starbucks and a LifeLab in the next door. Not to traffic before 3.00 PM. A lot of things in here. Perfect to come and get everything.

I basically found what I wanted on my own. But when I asked for help. Customer service person helped me right away. Very nice...and cashier was great and good to talk to.... but as usual you always end up buy what you didnt go there for. Like this watch for only $9.99!

Automotive Department Store We came by to check out their Black Friday sales event. I came to see the two household appliances that were advertised and scored excellent buys. Brightly lit aisles and well stocked displays. The microwave oven section was half empty but I managed to find a boxed Cuisinart air fryer convention toaster oven in stock as advertised at 50% off along with an additional $50 discount at the checkout! Wow! I also purchased a magic bullet brand personal blender on sale for $29.95. This place is a wonderful store for incredible buys. I come often to purchase specials from their flyers when there are things we need. The staff are helpful and knowledgeable. They publish and distribute a flyer every week or every other week depending on the season. This place is advertised as an automotive store but it has so much more to offer with a great selection of housewares, sporting goods and making your home beautiful. Well worth a visit.

I love their Christmas decor section. All the happy Christmas songs. Very festive arrangement and  free photo booth Inspired me to decorate my house very early. And now my neighbors are doing the same
I am impressed how clean the store and nicely decorated. Their washroom reminds me of my house every time my cleaner visits.
Great  customer service. I like their pots and pans section reasonable prices. Be careful  of  the quality of their producs. A much better choice than  Winners for dishes.

The largest selection of products out of any other Canadian Tire location Ive been to. Its very clean and tidy. As it should be for a newer location. Shopping atmosphere is calm and relaxing as a result of how spacious it is. The merchandising methods deployed also helps. Older gentlemen in auto parts is awesome. Knowledgable, kind and direct.

This location of Canadian Tire is one of the best location compared to what they used to have few decades ago. They are located independently along with other brand names like Sports Check, Best Buy, Marshals. There is a Starbucks and a LifeLab in the next door.

Today,  I went to this store to buy some portable BBQ and TENT for our camping and I was so grateful for RJ who assists me all through out. He was so knowledgable about the products and showed an excellent costumer service. I will definitely shop here again and hopefully RJ will be there when I come back.
I always visit this location. The staff are helpful, and the auto service department is top-notch. I do most of my household shopping here.

HUGE Canadian Tire! Lots of ample parking everywhere and they also have a good selection of live plants at this one but not as good as Cambie. What I really liked about this location is that they have their patio/outdoor furniture setup and on display. This way you can test out the furniture to see if it s what you were envisioning online. The other CTs don t really do this so this one was great for that. One thing though is this one doesn t have any self checkout stations and there was a huge lineup and only one person jumped on to another cashier to help the one cashier for the longest time. I m a fan of self checkouts for this reason.
I like this Canadian Tire location a lot, the staff is always friendly and knowledgeable. Great parking as well as a Starbucks nearby.
Fantastic store , they have everything and better price than Amazon,  see for yourself, plus friendly and professional people ready to help,  by supporting local business you support local economy

Best customer service by Michael. Took ownership to look for a part I was looking for, couldnt find it even in the storage. Offered to help me by calling other store. Thank you Michael for going above and beyond.

Canadian Tire handles auto inspections and RIV inspections with expert precision. Comfortable waiting area and convenient indoor parking spaces. Highly recommend their capable and friendly staff and I ll be coming back for basic auto needs and  guy toys  shopping for sure.

Scosche cell phone magnet holder for the car is extremely good quality. The magnet is much easier and convenient over other products. It s easy to reposition to eye level, and can hold any phone size. After three months of use when the product was super tight in the socket, I had a small issue by pulling the plug out on an angle too fast. Rather than fixing it, I returned it to the store with my triangle card and exchanged it for a new one. They found my receipt by tracking the purchase date. Very satisfied with service and auto accessories!
Had a few questions about my truck Staff were very knowledgeable and were really quick to help me!
Everything required for a house other than groceries,  vegetables and fruits under one roof. Best was gardening material.
I love this place for garden needs all the way to tools and activities for the kids. Tons of varieties for summer fun.
Helpful with choosing car tires. Answered all my questions thoroughly. Their assistance was nice.

One of the largest Canadian Tires I know. Loads of parking. Clean and well stocked. Easy to find where my items were located. If not, there is always help just around the corner. Will recommend especially for car lovers like my self the whole bottom section is for cars.
Helpful and Kind Staff!! Best Car accessories

If you want to get the best service at this Canadian Tire, Connor is the guy you should ask for help. I wanted to change my battery of my car today. I was so lucky to get Connors service. He asked a couple of questions to make sure I did need to change the battery. He even took his time to test the battery for me. When I decided to change the battery, he recommended the reasonable one for me. He also offered me two options to replace it: let their machinists do that for me (charge 68$) or by myself. In order to save the money, I chose to do that by myself.  I asked Connor to lent me the tools and tried it. Unfortunately, it was not as simple as I thought and gave it up, and I turned to the machinists for help, but none of them were available at that moment and asked me to leave my car there and they might replace it tomorrow. I was so disappointed and turned to Connor for help again. By the rule, Connor is not allowed to replace the battery for me, but he still be so nice to stand beside and guide me how to do that properly. With his instructions, I finally replace my battery. To be honest, I bothered Connor so many times today, but he was so patient and offered me the best service all the time! Connor, thank you so much for saving my day!

If you have the right car, use the curbside pick up if you have heavy items. Just do your part by clearing your car, and everything will go smoothly. They got the equipment to help you put it in your car. The guy that helped us was quick and knew what to do. We didnt have to wait long when we checked in at the designated spot -- approx. 5-10 minutes on a Sunday afternoon.
I always enjoy going to Canadian tire  they have everything you need and more    I just got my Audi A4 tires replaced. They did a good job!
Great selection of various products and clean branch, staffs are great willing to help. Fast check out time. Lots of free parking available on First and second floor.

The auto service was spectacular. Great prices and didnt change from when I called them. Reliable technicians and they had the skills to trouble shoot the problem. They called me when they encountered a problem and told me honestly why they had to trouble shoot the problem and what their recommendations were.  Ill definitely be going again. About $50 for changing winter tires with rims

I had an issue with a product that they are selling and they went above and beyond to help me figure out the defect and fix it. Multiple staff members helped and they were all really understanding, kind, and solution oriented. I was so happy with the service they provided!
Big, annoying to have to go up and down but overall good location
So easy to pop in and quickly get what you need. There is plenty of parking too.
Getting an oil change and tune up. I talked with the front desk person who took my information and I am all set to take my car in and have the work done. No problems all went well.
Great place to shop for automotive needs, home and garden etc. Occasional kitchenware is great too. This Canadian Tire is really in the middle of nowhere. Plenty of parking to work with.

I went to this Canadian tire and asked for helped and the employee helped and even went into the warehouse to look for my product, didn t give up until he found what I was looking for. Service was great! Store has a big great selection of products that I don t get where I live. I was really satisfied with the service and store layout. Lots of parking, wheelchair accessible with elevators.
Big place, clean and lots of options. But I really like to Male white manager (Forgot his name) his always been helpful and friendly. Upstairs department.

We went to the Marine Drive and Ontario Steet store. What a pleasant customer service. We were pushed around by the other  two stores in Richmond such as no, we cannot accept other store rain cheques, or the rain cheques are good for 30 days, no extension.  This Marine Drive store has a lot of inventory, accept other stores rain cheques. The cashier and the manager were polite and friendly. Keep up with the good customer service please especially in this stressful period of the economy. People deserve to be treated well and vice verses.

Tons of free parking. Totally wheelchair accessible. This is a good store to come to for all kinds of housewares. Pro tip: look up the item you want online to find out what aisle number to find it in. Otherwise it is such a big store, you will be shopping all the aisles.

Auto department was very well managed. Extremely comfortable and lovely open concept for a waiting room. This location does have underground parking, 2 floor levels. 1st floor being your typical canadian tire store, the 2nd floor being the auto department. which is nice it makes shopping super easy especially if your the type of shopper to get in and get out.

Free parking underground, 2 levels at this store, need to use elevators. Service is excellent at this location! Super friendly and helpful. Found everything we were looking for, great location, will be back.

You can find everything here even electrical and plumbing supplies. Theyve greatly improved their returns process. I find it way easier to return now when compared to last year. However, theyre still a little bit more room to get to hassle free returns status like their competitors. Good to see they continue to strive to enhance their customers experience.

5 stars for Joe and Pat in the Service Department! They always provide top notch service and I have never felt pressured or strong armed into anything. They provide friendly customer service every time.
Really big store carry so many thing
Found all the items I went there for. Including sale items. Im impressed that they still have hand sanitizer at the door.

First time at this location and was impressed. Great customer service, staff were helpful and friendly. Extra thanks to Brian who assisted us with baby strollers and we bought one. Clean store, Covid protocols in place. Plus theres a Party City within the store!
Recently shopped for hiking gear. Very pleased

Came in looking to cut some house keys the kid who directed me to where i needed to go could have cared less about giving me proper directions and really only cared about restocking shelves. Kind of a joke. However the guy at the automotive booth was amazing. He multi-tasked cutting my keys and ringing up other customers was pleasant and talkative and went above and beyond! That should be your next employee of the month!  Operator #: 605123. Give this guy a raise and a promotion!!!

Well stocked. Had exactly what I wanted at a good price. Bought an air compressor because I had a slow leak in a tire. Great product. Great price (on sale - under $50). Worked a treat. Also had the dome light for my ten year old car in stock. Opened till 9pm on Sunday. Just an all round win for Canadian tire.

Like this marine drive location. Good parking. Stock always there specially the sale items. Very convenient as it is closer to super store. When buy groceries can pick up stuff from here at the same time save me a trip
Tons of product , pretty well organized.  Huge store with good parking.
A variety of products. Really good and good service too.

Seems like i have been to most CanTire stores in Vancouver; a real go to when you are looking for general supplies and you can almost be guaranteed that it will be here in stock. This location is large and has everything and is full service. Seasonal stuff is out for Xmas already and the location is clean and well organized. Would come again.

Was looking for a starter bike for my special needs son and Sachi, Manager at the Canadian Tire on Marine Drive was so very helpful and patient.  We purchased the bike we were looking for.  I am so appreciative to Sachi for his expertise to explain and for being understanding with my son.  Thank you, Sachi!

Had a great experience with buying a new rim for my car, then having the tire taken off old rim & put on new. Louis from the Automotive Dept, went the extra for me to set things up where I was very appreciative! Had great service along with friendly...! Definitely be going back!

I shop here regularly so when I went in to do a big spring garden shopping I figured I may as well apply for the points credit card. There was a technical issue with the printer and while the credit card company was NOT AT ALL helpful in troubleshooting the issue so that I could get points on that purchase, the in-store staff went above and beyond to help me out. Special thanks to Ranjot Nagra who was patient and competent and made sure that I was happy before I left the store. Could have been a real nightmare and Im still really mad about the credit companys customer service representatives complete lack of customer service, but the Canadian Tire staff at the front desk and in the garden department were really lovely.
Good for purchasing home needs, garden needs, carpentry needs, garage needs, car equipment, workers equipment, kitchen items, etc.

A good selection of products.  Staff has always been very helpful.  We find  Canadian Tire sale prices are better than most.  I prefer because of the parking.  When you do make a purchase it is easy to take to the car and load.  Great kitchen supply selection that the wife likes. Check out the kitchen small appliances and other goodies.   Watch for sale prices.  Sometime they are up to 70% lower than competition.  Worth a visit.

I shop fairly routinely at Canadian Tire and even got m y last set of tires here. The store has practically everything! I can always find my SodaStream flavours, for example, whereas most other businesses have no selection.
Awesome place for Christmas  shopping

The staff were very helpful and friendly. The store was very organized, clean and well stocked. I enjoyed my shopping experience and I highly recommend people go there for just about almost everything one needs in todays demanding lifestyle.

Parking is ample and theres fun car-shaped carts if you have kids. Stock is always plentiful and the seasonal stuff is good, too. Floor staff are plentiful and easy to find, which cant be said for all locations. Theyre generally very knowledgeable and have pointed me in the right direction.

Had some tires installed recently, and was very impressed with the service provided by two employees in the auto department - Joe and Louis. They certainly went above and beyond. Tires were mounted, balanced, and installed within 30 minutes. Extremely happy with my visit! Thanks!

Love, so much about this place. If you go to the car section ladies you will find terry cloths to dry cars BUT EVEN BETTER use these on your DISHES for drying as there is nothing more absorbent then these for dishcloths. This store has friendly cashiers and lovely return policies.
I love the products here and service is awesome
I was glad to know this Canadian tire has a dedicated garden center. Found everything I was looking for. Some nice deals.
Staff and customer service was amazing will definitely drive out of my way to go to this store again :)

I shop here often. I feel that alot of the young employees need a bit more training on helping customers. Often times when I ask they dont know what Im looking for and then I find it. I rated well cuz its big they have what I need. Just train the young employees better.
The parts manager  mark was extremely helpful in finding my battery for my volkswagen rabbit. Took battery to my car aswell, plus hes a pro pubg player

Everybody was extremely kind and helpful to help me find this bike Ive been wanting! - I live far from the area and this was the only location which had it in stock, so customer service and the manager very kindly offered to assemble it and have it ready for pick up the next day. Really made my whole experience a blast. Thank you guys!

This Canadian Tire location service department is very efficient.  Joe confirmed tires were in stock & put on hold, appointment time was accommodating, installation was fast, and price was exactly as quoted.  Best part about this service department is they listen & do not use high pressure sell tactics.  Will recommend others and will come again
I love items on clearance here

Now I had just come from a bad experience at the Canadian Tire Burnaby Byrne road location where I found a salesman named Mark at the Marine and Ontario location. I phoned and asked if he had a particular tire I needed.  He said yes it says we have a set but let me check before you get there.  He came back on the line and said yes they are in stock. I told him I would be there in ten minutes.  When I arrived he had them waiting on a cart.  I paid for them and he helped load them in my truck. Now this was a great experience.   Mark I really appreciate the great customer service.  Thanks.

This is my go-to place for auto services. Ive been a customer since theyve opened and have never been wronged by the service team. Joe and Pat have always treated me in the utmost professional manner. You might have heard of all the horror CT stories and Im sure most are true. However, I believe this store is definitely an exception. To the CT auto service team, keep up the great work!

This is the usual Canadian tire store that I go to, sometimes I go here to get pots for planting things, other times they come here to get the odd tool or something, maybe a hammer, maybe a ladder, I have once even came here and got some pants. And I was an exciting time. They have red bowls at the counter which is nice, one time I bought a cigarette lighter plug adapted compressor. But it broke after the first use, I was unhappy so I took it back to Canadian tire and they gave me a full refund, no questions asked, good time

Was a well organized and well stocked store. Was a bit of a walk to get to from the bus, and the regular store is on the upper level so you have to take the elevator if you have no car. Was clean and had what I was looking for in stock.
Good collection of general machandise
Best store Best service   and delivery and lady manager good service if you got a mistake or problem.
Brock went above and beyond with Customer Service experience today. You cant get the friendly interaction online only in person. Will definitely be telling my friends and family to shop at this CT.

Every time Ive been there customer service is top notch. Unbeatable. Staff is super friendly and I wouldnt save a lot of staff but plenty. Every time you look for someone  it doesnt take long to find.

I always visit Canadian Tire to buys plants and  other household  items, every time my doctor send me for blood work coz Life Labs is within the compound of CT. There you can find varieties of house and garden plants.
Very clean and organized store, Mark in the automotive department parts is very helpful and knowledgeable,he makes sure you find what you are looking for.

Andrew, a mechanic in the shop was awesome. A surprise to me, my car wouldnt start up (with no prior warnings of issues). Although Andrew was the only mechanic working in shop, he stepped out for a minute to have a look and give my battery a boost. Great guy!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Danielle, we appreciate the 5-star review! Corporate Customer Experience Team

reviews.review_text: Got a flat tire.  Every placed is closed due to the long weekend.  I noticed Canadian Tire was open so I gave them a call.  Joe from the Automotive Service Department answered and told me to bring my vehicle in.  He said that it would probably take a few hours because they have quite a few vehicles in for servicing today.  He managed to somehow squeeze me in and had me back on the road in under an hour.  I cant thank Joe enough.  From the turnaround time to the service to the professionalism, I am extremely satisfied.  Joe and the Asian Mechanic with the blonde highlights (Sorry I didnt catch his name) was amazing.  Thank you once again :)
Clean and well kept and stocked Canadian Tire. Entrance off of upper parking. Bigger store, but is well marked and staff are friendly.
Its wonderful store, you can get many things there!!!
Overall I have been here multiple times and always had a good service. No major complaints, whatever you need they have and its overall a nice and clean store. Very convenient.

Great customer service at this location. Great attitude and willingness to help. I didnt catch the young mans name but helped me with obtaining 4 bags of fireplace pellets from the backroom. Thanks buddy
I always shop in canadian Tires friendly staff and prices.
Huge store, clean, organized and items in stock and a very friendly, efficient cashier (everything that the  Richmond stores dont offer!)......worth the drive over the bridge.
Shelves well stocked! Absolutely well stocked shelves for Spring. Clean Store. Fantastic Store Manager - Brock. Jam packed stacked up summer readiness for All.

Well where to begin, canadian tire has been a hugh part of my life , ever since i was young remember going there with my dad getting what we need for car and working on the car in parking lot . Now i have seen alot of repairs on my own vehicles over the years and spentalot of time wrenching my trucks in the parking lot just like my dad would do . And my favorite part as a kid was getting to keep the canadian tire money. Over the years its been growing into a great all round needs kinda store there house brand is become very compeditive with the big name power tools and at a price way below which is a good thing for the low budget people or if you are just a tight wad like my self . They have a great spray paint selection for those small paint jobs or brush on or larger sprayer paints as well as all your paint accessories.  The auto motive section is large and user friendly lay out for the self serve types or if you need help well good luck on fast service and when you get it its rare to find an employee wllling to solve your needs if they dont have what you need .that being said  i think over all this world would not be the same without canadian tire . Im glad its there for my needs . I highly recomend this store for someone who has not already experianced the good this store has .
Great selection. Wonderful and very hhlelpful staff. Bought a new toilet. Was ready for pick up in under 3 min. Loved it

I have had two exceptional customer service experiences at the Automotive department. The mechanics are very helpful and the service is very good! I always leave feeling good about the experience. I really appreciate the fact that they go above and beyond for their customers! Thank you :)
This CT branch is big & modern, up to date. Well stocked with well-trained staff.  Only thing, the automotive section is physically separate from main store. Minor inconvenience.
I love the service a lot and the staff/workers there are very nice, helpful and friendly. There is a lot of amazing things here and the store is clean, neat and great overall.

Canadian Tire stores around the Vancouver lower main land have been going through some renovations. This is a brilliant opportunity to find great deals on clearance sales as the store shifts its shelves they have lowered prices on items that have not been selling or the remainder of seasonal products. This is a wonderful store with great staff members who greet you when you arrive, help you find whatever you need while you are there and assist you when you are leaving. There are a couple of really amazing managers who treat the customers well and the staff seem content which probably means they are given the respect they deserve. All in all Canadian Tire is my favorite store and it is amazing that this fanchise has given their customers rewards since the begining. Canadian Tire money is the first reward system and that has changed our retail experience because now all stores have reward programs. This is a great sorce of pride for this corporation and a part of our culture which protrays a national identity which we all can be excited to be a part of. Support this store and you will not be dissapointed but rather fulfilled with quality and reasonably priced products.
Good price and service on the retail side. Got some bad experience with their tire department though in a different location in Richmond, although the name is Canadian tire

Great service, any time I need to find something they will go out of there way to find it.  I had to return something and didnt have a receipt and the lady made it happen for an exchange.  Great place great stuff!
Everything you need is here but some things are expensive. They have some clearance and offer
Can now pick up from locker, and always have weekly deals and triangle perks. Now I can even duplicate keys here self serve.

I normally dread going to any Canadian Tire. But this was a pleasant surprise. Even though there was an issue with the item I wanted, the manager went above and beyond to make eveything right and all the staff were super helpful. Thanks for handling a problem so well!
One of the best Canadian tire stores. Helpful staff and very nice environment. However, Canadian tire in general, is not always up to date and you cant find latest products.
